|Monks
|'''Danny Robins'''
|13 May 2014
|30 mins
|Gary Woodcroft ([[Seann Walsh]]) is in his late 20s and has never done a single useful thing in his life. He's been the living definition of the word 'chillax', straddling a narrow line between unemployed and unemployable. Then, after years of dubious benefit claiming, he finds himself finally threatened with prosecution. Faced with the real prospect of prison, he decides to do what anyone would... run away and hide in his local monastery. Also starring [[James Fleet]] as the Abbot.
